It was no part of the scribe’s business while chronicling the Warrington tenants and possessions, to indulge in dis- quisitions on natural history, —and accordingly the notices he has left us on this subject are few, and very meagre. We learn from him, however, that the Austin friars had a walled orchard, well stocked with fruit trees3 buthe does not inform us what the fruit trees were.
